    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of the great Songhai trading state of West Africa (flourished 15th-16th century), located on the Niger River in what is now central Mali, and eventually extending west to the Atlantic coast and east into Niger and Nigeria.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
